The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of domination-type problems, which are typically studied in the area of discrete mathematics and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses coding theory problems, which fall under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The use of parameterized complexity techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the categories of Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
